        <p class="resource-subtitle">Step-by-step instructions to set up your learning environment</p>
    </div>

    <div class="resource-content">
        <section class="quick-start">
            <h2>Quick Start (5 minutes)</h2>
            <div class="steps">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">1</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Create Your Profile</h3>
                        <p>Complete your learner profile with your background and learning goals</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">2</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Watch Welcome Video</h3>
                        <p>Watch the program introduction and overview</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">3</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Take Induction Quiz</h3>
                        <p>Complete the induction assessment to assess your baseline knowledge</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="environment-setup">
            <h2>Setting Up Your Environment</h2>
            
            <div class="setup-section">
                <h3>System Requirements</h3>
                <ul class="requirements-list">
                    <li>Windows 10+, macOS 10.14+, or Linux (Ubuntu 18.04+)</li>
                    <li>4GB RAM minimum (8GB recommended)</li>
                    <li>2GB free disk space</li>
                    <li>Reliable internet connection</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="setup-section">
                <h3>Install Python</h3>
                <ol class="install-steps">
                    <li>Download Python 3.9 or later from <code>python.org</code></li>
                    <li>Run the installer and select "Add Python to PATH"</li>
                    <li>Verify installation: <code>python --version</code></li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="setup-section">
                <h3>Install Required Libraries</h3>
                <p>Open terminal/command prompt and run:</p>
                <code class="code-block">pip install numpy pandas jupyter matplotlib scikit-learn</code>
            </div>

            <div class="setup-section">
                <h3>Launch Jupyter Notebook</h3>
                <p>In your terminal, run:</p>
                <code class="code-block">jupyter notebook</code>
                <p>This will open Jupyter in your browser at <code>localhost:8888</code></p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="platform-tour">
            <h2>Platform Tour</h2>
            <div class="tour-items">
                <div class="tour-item">
                    <h3>Learning Dashboard</h3>
                    <p>Access all course modules, track progress, and view your achievements</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tour-item">
                    <h3>Code Sandbox</h3>
                    <p>Write and run Python code directly in the browser</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tour-item">
                    <h3>Resources</h3>
                    <p>Download materials, guides, and code examples</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tour-item">
                    <h3>Community</h3>
                    <p>Connect with peers and instructors in discussion forums</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="troubleshooting">
            <h2>Common Issues</h2>
            <div class="faq-items">
                <details>
                    <summary>Python not recognized in terminal</summary>
                    <p>Make sure you selected "Add Python to PATH" during installation. Restart your terminal and try again.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Jupyter won't start</summary>
                    <p>Try: <code>pip install --upgrade jupyter</code> then run <code>jupyter notebook</code> again</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Can't import libraries</summary>
                    <p>Verify installation: <code>pip list</code> should show numpy, pandas, etc. If missing, reinstall with pip</p>
                </details>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="next-steps">
            <h2>Next Steps</h2>
            <p>Once you've completed setup, proceed to:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Module 1: Program Overview</li>
                <li>Module 1: Course Navigation</li>
                <li>Module 1: Environment Setup</li>
                <li>Module 1: Induction Assessment</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>

